You are implementing audit API routes for the video pipeline:
- `app/api/pipeline/audit/run/route.ts`
- `app/api/pipeline/audit/results/route.ts`

Requirements
1. Register `registerExecutor("audit", ...)` at module load in the run route.
2. Audit executor behavior (per selected section):
   - Resolve target sections from `params.sections`; if omitted, audit all `loadProject().sections`.
   - Read section spec files from `section.specDir`, including only `.md` files that do not start with `AUDIT_`.
   - For each spec file:
     - Render still image to `outputs/audit/{sectionId}/{specName}_frame.png`.
     - Compute frame as `Math.floor((section.durationSeconds / 2) * (loadProject().render.fps ?? 30))`.
     - Call `runClaudeAnalysis(prompt, onLog)` and treat `analysis.severity === "pass"` as pass, otherwise fail.
     - Write `specs/{sectionId}/AUDIT_{specName}.md` with format:
       `## Verdict\n{pass|fail}\n## Summary\n{text}\n`.
   - Emit per-section SSE events:
     `{ type: "audit-section", sectionId, status: "running" | "done" | "error", passCount, failCount }`.
   - Run section audits concurrently with `Promise.all`.
3. `POST /api/pipeline/audit/run`:
   - Accept JSON `{ sections?: string[] }` and tolerate invalid/non-JSON body by defaulting to `{}`.
   - Start `runPipelineStage("audit", { sections: body.sections }, send)` asynchronously.
   - Stream SSE using `data: <json>\n\n` format.
   - Emit `{ type: "job", jobId }` on success, or `{ type: "error", message }` on failure.
   - Return SSE headers: `Content-Type: text/event-stream`, `Cache-Control: no-cache`, `Connection: keep-alive`.
4. `GET /api/pipeline/audit/results`:
   - Load sections via `loadProject()`.
   - For each section, read `AUDIT_*.md` files from `section.specDir`.
   - Parse markdown headings `## Verdict` and `## Summary`.
   - Return:
     - `sections: AuditSectionResult[]`
     - `AuditSectionResult = { sectionId: string; sectionLabel: string; passCount: number; failCount: number; status: "done" | "pending" | "error"; specs: SpecAuditResult[] }`
     - `SpecAuditResult = { specName: string; verdict: "PASS" | "FAIL"; summary: string; finding?: string; specPath?: string }`
   - Status logic: `"pending"` when no audit files exist but section spec markdown files exist; otherwise `"done"`.
   - If an audit file cannot be parsed, include a `"FAIL"` spec entry with summary `"Error parsing audit report"`.
   - `specPath` must be compatible with `/api/pipeline/specs/file` by starting with `specs/` (without double prefixing).
5. No authentication checks.

